@page "/"

<PageTitle>Home</PageTitle>

<h1>OIDC Demo Application</h1>

<p class="lead">
    This application demonstrates authentication and authorization using a custom
    OpenID Connect identity provider.
</p>

<hr />

<h3>What this demo shows</h3>

<ul>
    <li>Login and logout using standard OIDC flows</li>
    <li>Authenticated user information via claims and the UserInfo endpoint</li>
    <li>Access tokens issued by the identity provider</li>
    <li>Calling a protected API using bearer tokens</li>
</ul>

<h3>How to use the demo</h3>

<ol>
    <li>Sign in using the login button in the top-right corner</li>
    <li>Visit the <strong>Profile</strong> page to view user information</li>
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Weather</strong> to call a protected API endpoint</li>
    <li>Sign out to observe authentication state changes</li>
</ol>

<p>
    This client uses the built-in Blazor WebAssembly OIDC authentication library to
    verify compatibility with existing frameworks.
</p>